the impression of color by pressing one’s upper eyelid. On occasion I allow myself the luxury of imagining today’s world, our machines, our fashions, as they will appear to our descendants four or five hundred years hence. I assure you that I feel as ancient as a Renaissance monk.”

“Have some more wine, my dear Simpson,” offered the Colonel.

